wiki.content: "내 방을 여행하는 법" (Fly To My Room) is a song by Suga, J-Hope, Jimin and V of BTS. It was released on November 20, 2020 and appears as the second track for BTS' seventh mini album BE by [art ist]BTS ([art ist]방탄소년단) The second track of BTS' seventh mini-album BE, "Fly To My Room" is a 1990s-inspired R&B and pop song with neo soul and synth-pop elements. Performed by Jimin, V, J-Hope, and Suga, it features "breathy" vocals and falsettos with the former two switching back and forth in the verses and chorus, and the latter two rapping in a "sing-song" style. The song relies on a "sparse, laid-back production" for which '70s piano, funky keyboards, and drum beats provide minimalist instrumentation and sports a staccato-style melody. Lyrically, the track addresses loneliness and confinement speaking about mentally being able to travel to escape the monotony of quarantine life. Read more on Last.fm.
